The Chronicle Bongani Ndlovu, Showbiz Reporter
Rapper, model and dancer Noreen Moira is upbeat about sharing the stage with South Africa’s Cassper Nyovest, Amaroto and NaakMusiQ in Bulawayo on Sunday. Dubbed the Sunday Summer “Big Boys Party”, the concert will be held at Khumalo Hockey Stadium and will also feature the likes of P.O.Y and King98. Born Nokuthaba Makhwelo, Noreen said she was excited to be part of the show and will grab at the opportunity to impress. “This is such a big opportunity for me as it’ll be my first time sharing the stage with international acts like Casper Nyovest, Amaroto and NaakMusiQ. I’m bringing my A-game and practising very hard for my performance.  This is definitely going to boost my career in a very big way,” Moira said. The 22-year-old said she has three songs to her name, Truth, BadA** and Bongo that features Loshy. “I’ve three songs that are available on YouTube. I’m definitely working on something new that’ll be released in April,” said Moira. The up-and-coming artiste started dancing when she was in secondary school in Bulawayo’s Emganwini suburb, where she resides. She was part of the group Whine Queens and has in the past said she wants to take over the scene. This upcoming show will certainly catapult her to fame if she utilises it well.